in the sense that any project of this magnitude, right, which is quite expensive,

00:55:01.820 --> 00:55:05.979
has to have a very well thought of strategy, right? So it all begins with the business case.

00:55:05.979 --> 00:55:10.939
How do we put together a compelling business case so that the stakeholders understand the value of

00:55:10.939 --> 00:55:16.860
the project? And as part of the business case, you have to provide the justification. And then

00:55:16.860 --> 00:55:23.179
what we also did is we provided a pretty valid, pretty solid value proposition in the sense that

00:55:23.820 --> 00:55:27.820
through the years, what is the kind of ROI you would get out of it, right? So we want to show

00:55:27.820 --> 00:55:34.219
that we do break even at X number of years, right? And then after that, you show like a positive ROI.

00:55:34.219 --> 00:55:39.820
And the way you show ROI is what is the time saved? What is the efficiency gained? And even

00:55:39.820 --> 00:55:44.300
compliance, right? That could also be an ROI. And all these things can be translated to dollar

00:55:44.300 --> 00:55:47.899
amount. What is the cost of non-compliance, right? So you can translate all that to about

00:55:47.899 --> 00:55:53.179
dollar amount and show the positive ROI at a certain point of time. So those things would

00:55:53.179 --> 00:55:58.620
be what would sort of convince the sponsor to say that, yes, this project is a go ahead.

